<subSubSection lastPageId="192" lastPageNumber="193" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="191.[151,1437,1194,2011]" lastBlockId="192.[151,1437,151,392]" lastPageId="192" lastPageNumber="193" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1878,1903]" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[668,789,1878,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colimae">
<emphasis box="[668,789,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">A. colimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the clypeus short and without a median tooth; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the mandible with the lower tooth longer than the others; the frons 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[1252,1375,1914,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriaceous">coriaceous</taxonomicName>
, with the punctures distinct; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle forming a right angle; the ocelli small; the pronotal disc with its transverse pronotal carina incomplete; the metapostnotal-propodeal suture convergent to the first metapostnotal carina; the mesopleural suture opened; the basivolsela without an apical excavation at the inner margin and without a short basal projection; the cuspis arms long; and the aedeagus basal portion wide, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colimae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="192" pageNumber="193">A. colimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the clypeus long and with a median tooth; the antennal scrobe carinate, but weak; the mandible with the teeth equally wide; the frons strongly 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[616,740,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="192" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriaceous">coriaceous</taxonomicName>
; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle acute; the ocelli large; the pronotal disc with its transverse pronotal carina complete; the metapostnotal-propodeal suture straight; the mesopleural suture closed; the basivolsela with an apical excavation at the inner margin and with a short basal projection; the cuspis arms short; and the aedeagus basal portion slender.
</paragraph>
